-- Valdespin, Davis Hit Home Runs to Lead Mets to 3-1 Win Over Cubs
-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 2012-07-08T05:03:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-08/valdespin-davis-hit-home-runs-to-lead-mets-to-3-1-win-over-cubs.html
Jordany Valdespin and  Ike Davis  hit
home runs to lead the New Mets to a 3-1 victory over the  Chicago
Cubs  in a Major League Baseball contest.  Valdespin hit a solo home run in the second inning and
Davis drove home Ruben Tejada with his homer in the third at
Citi Field in New York.  David DeJesus hit a one-run single in the sixth for the
Cubs only score.  Dillon Gee (6-7) gave up one run on seven hits and struck
out four in eight innings for the Mets. Bobby Parnell got his
second save, allowing one hit and striking out one in the final
inning.  “Today was all about command of his breaking ball and
changeup,” Mets Manager Terry Collins said of Gee. “He pitched
really good today.”  Jeff Samardzija (6-8) allowed three runs and seven hits,
while striking out four in seven innings.  The Mets (46-39) are in second place, 4 ½ games behind the
 Washington Nationals  in the five-team  National League East . The
Cubs are in sixth place in the six-team NL Central, 15 games
behind the Pittsburgh Pirates.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nancy Kercheval in Washington at 
